2\. Critical Items --- Resolved by RMC

2.1 CRITICAL-001: Early Retirement Reduction Rates

**Status: FULLY RESOLVED --- Direct RMC Citation Obtained**

**RMC Section:** §18-409(b) --- Early retirement

The RMC contains the actual statutory reduction tables, which
definitively confirm the rates previously verified against three DERP
member-facing sources:

**Members Employed Before July 1, 2011 (Tiers 1 & 2): 3% per year under
65**

  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  **Age at Retirement**               **% of Normal Benefit**

  Under 55                            0%

  55                                  70%

  56                                  73%

  57                                  76%

  58                                  79%

  59                                  82%

  60                                  85%

  61                                  88%

  62                                  91%

  63                                  94%

  64                                  97%

  65                                  100%
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------

**Members First Employed On or After July 1, 2011 (Tier 3): 6% per year
under 65**

  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------
  **Age at Retirement**               **% of Normal Benefit**

  Under 60                            0%

  60                                  70%

  61                                  76%

  62                                  82%

  63                                  88%

  64                                  94%

  65                                  100%
  ----------------------------------- -----------------------------------

**Impact:** Case 2 (Jennifer Kim) previously recalculated with corrected
3% rate. RMC now provides the definitive statutory authority. The table
also confirms reduction is by completed years only (integer age), not
prorated by months.

2.2 CRITICAL-002: Employer Contribution Rate

**Status: FULLY RESOLVED --- Direct RMC Citation Obtained**

**RMC Section:** §18-407(e)(1) and §18-407(f)(1)

The RMC states: Effective January 1, 2023, employer contributes 17.95%
and employee contributes 8.45% of gross salary. Total combined rate:
26.40%. Our earlier project documents used 11% for employer rate, which
was likely the rate circa 2005-2010. The seed data generator should use
era-appropriate rates.

